A group of activists wants President Uhuru Kenyatta to either act on the runaway corruption that has plagued Kenya or resign.The group told a press briefing in Nairobi on Tuesday that they want immediate legal action against those guilty of the crime.Activist Boniface Mwangi said they will stage a demonstration at Freedom Corner on Thursday in a push for action by Uhuru. Kenyans have been subjected to theft and plunder of public resources and the President has been silent for a long time," noted Mwangi."We urge all Kenyans to show up at Uhuru Park to support the fight against corruption."[VIDEO] Frustrated Uhuru scolds state officials on rampant corruptionThe activists said they were frustrated that Uhuru has not acted on corruption, which they noted has drowned the country. Mr President stop claiming you have done your part in fighting the corruption menace. Sack ineffective officials and if that is not possible, resign, said Kipng eno Rono.The group, which included members of Haki Centre, KHRC, Maskani ya Taifa, Third Wheel Alliance and TI-Kenya, recommended convictions and prison sentences.They noted the President promised this during Mashujaa Day celebrations on October 20.The activists also want suspects' assets frozen to prevent illegal funds transfers.They also asked the government to reform the justice system and organisations charged with fighting corruption to build trust among citizens.Uhuru was also asked to separate corruption from politics and ensure corrupt individuals are dealt with personally.The protests comes amid investigations into the Sh791 million National Youth Service scandal and the alleged theft of Sh5 billion at the Health ministry.Read: Frustrated MPs turn to Bible verses during Josephine Kabura NYS scam grillingAlso read: Kenyans outraged over Uhuru kin links to Sh5 billion 'Mafia House' scandal